Czech Stocks: Erste Group, Komercni Banka, New World Resources

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-08-04T15:03:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/czech-stocks-ecm-real-estate-new-world-resources-shares-move.html
The Czech Republic’s PX stock gauge
fell the most in seven months, sliding 2.2 percent to 1,120.7 at
its 4:28 p.m. end of trading in Prague. It was the third day of
declines and the lowest close since Nov. 30.  The following were among the most active equities on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   plunged 5.3 percent to 704.5
koruna, the biggest drop in two months and the lowest close
since September. European stocks sank, with lenders among the
biggest decliners, amid deepening concern that the global
recovery is stalling.  Komercni Banka AS (KOMB)   retreated 2.4 percent to 3,600
koruna, its lowest close in more than a year. Credit Suisse
Group AG cut its share-price estimate for the Czech unit of
Societe Generale SA to 3,850 koruna from 4,200 koruna.  New World Resources Plc (NWR CP), the country’s largest
coking-coal producer, fell the most in three months, closing
down 6.1 percent at 201 koruna. Mining companies led declines in
European stocks and oil fell for a fifth day amid concern the
global economy will slow down.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  